stylometry: The factors that much be considered is how much demand must be met and how much lead time is needed. The user should also consider how much safety stock they have so they can make an accurate decision. The trade off is that excess inventory means incurring holding costs but not having enough inventory means missing out on potential sales. Therefore, the user must be careful to estimate how much demand will need met and how much lead time the order will need to arrive in order to have the right amount of inventory.
